Dr Obert Mpofu Chronicle Reporter ZANU-PF’s secretary for Administration Dr Obert Mpofu has called on all Politburo members to attend an Extraordinary Politburo meeting at 10AM in Harare today. The meeting will be held at the party’s national headquarters and all members are expected to attend. The party’s Secretary for Information and Publicity Cde Simon Khaya Moyo did not outline the meeting’s main agenda. The meeting comes at a time when the ruling party is gearing for its primary elections set for May 5 and when the provinces have submitted their curriculum vitaes for aspiring candidates to the Commissariat for vetting.